Description: Clay sealing of a document: stamped with a cartouche containing a hieroglyphic inscription naming Necho. On the reverse an impression of the papyrus document to which it was attached. Buff to black

Hall 1913 / Catalogue of Egyptian scarabs, etc. in the British Museum (p.291, nos. 2783-2784; p.294, no. 2804) (for form)
